325
00:26:25,631 --> 00:26:27,540


326
00:26:33,137 --> 00:26:36,222
- 这是什么? - 这是红外线望远镜
- What is this? - It's an infrared scope.

327
00:26:36,307 --> 00:26:38,976
狙击手的夜视工具
<i>Snipers use it for night vision.</i>

328
00:26:39,060 --> 00:26:40,720
我们拿它做什么?
What are we gonna do with it?

329
00:26:40,812 --> 00:26:42,721
爬过去查看装了铁条的地下室窗户
Get a look in those barred- up basement windows.

330
00:26:42,814 --> 00:26:44,890


331
00:26:47,652 --> 00:26:50,735
我们不应该这样做
I've been thinking about it. I don't think we should go through with this.

332
00:26:50,821 --> 00:26:52,231
你是胆小鬼吗?
Are you a 'fraidy cat?

333
00:26:52,322 --> 00:26:55,240
我只是觉得太过头了
No, I just think things have gone off the deep end.

334
00:26:55,325 --> 00:26:59,572
红外线夜视望远镜? 接下来要窃听电话吗?
Infrared night vision scopes? What are we gonna do next, tap their phone?

335
00:26:59,663 --> 00:27:01,572
那可以安排
That can be arranged.

336
00:27:01,665 --> 00:27:04,416
最后就剩下在他们前院烧一个十字架
Then all we have to do is burn a cross on their front lawn.

337
00:27:04,501 --> 00:27:05,912


338
00:27:06,002 --> 00:27:08,920
- 安静 - 你听到什么?
- Quiet. - You hear that?

339
00:27:09,005 --> 00:27:10,914
我以为只有我听到
<i>I thought that was just me.</i>

340
00:27:11,006 --> 00:27:13,758
- 那是一种低频率的哼声 - 越来越大声
- It's a low-frequency hum or something. - It's getting louder.

341
00:27:13,843 --> 00:27:16,416
你听
Listen.

342
00:27:16,512 --> 00:27:19,264
那是变压器还是什么的?
Is that a transformer or something?

343
00:27:19,348 --> 00:27:21,257
该死的电力公司
The goddam power company.

344
00:27:21,350 --> 00:27:25,099
可是我不能...从哪里传来的?
But I can't... Where is it coming from?

345
00:27:25,187 --> 00:27:28,687
我知道从哪里传来的
<i>I know where it's coming from.</i>

346
00:28:00,053 --> 00:28:02,130


347
00:28:02,222 --> 00:28:04,464
搞什么鬼啊?
<i>What the hell was that?</i>

348
00:28:04,558 --> 00:28:05,969
部分停电
Brownout.

349
00:28:06,059 --> 00:28:08,977
那味道闻起来好像在煮猫
Smells like they're cooking a goddam cat over there.

350
00:28:09,062 --> 00:28:13,106
- 我要去一探究竟 - 蹲下!
- I'm gonna go find out what exactly... - Get down, get down!

351
00:28:34,753 --> 00:28:37,670
没有车前灯
No headlights.

352
00:30:12,796 --> 00:30:15,321
我可以想像新闻报导说
I can see the news report now:

353
00:30:15,515 --> 00:30:19,098
他们一家很安静 独来独往
"They were a quiet family. Kept pretty much to themselves.

354
00:30:19,186 --> 00:30:23,764
没有人怀疑他们正在搞鬼
No one would have ever suspected them of foul play."

355
00:30:26,860 --> 00:30:31,770
我从来没有看过人把自己的垃圾开到路边
I've never seen anybody drive their garbage to the street...

356
00:30:31,864 --> 00:30:33,773
然后拿一根棍子勐敲乱打
and then bang the hell out of it with a stick.

357
00:30:33,866 --> 00:30:36,701
从来没看过
I've never seen that.

358
00:30:43,375 --> 00:30:45,949
我们应该去看看 垃圾桶里面到底有什么
I say we get a look in those garbage cans.

359
00:30:46,045 --> 00:30:49,958
我可能太小心了 可是那样不是有点可疑?
Call me overly cautious, but don't you think that's a bit suspicious?

360
00:30:50,048 --> 00:30:53,464
在晚上十一点下大雨的时候翻他们的垃圾筒?
The three of us going through their garbage at 11:00 at night in the middle of a rainstorm?

361
00:30:53,551 --> 00:30:56,801
说得对 垃圾跑不了的
Affirmative. That garbage is going nowhere.

362
00:30:56,888 --> 00:30:59,805
明天一早在看也不迟 望远镜还我
I say we wait 'til first light. Scope me.

363
00:30:59,891 --> 00:31:02,643
我要走了
<i>I'm outta here.</i>

364
00:31:05,313 --> 00:31:07,471
下雨延期
Rain delay.

365
00:31:07,565 --> 00:31:10,601
真倒楣
Bummer.

366
00:31:19,910 --> 00:31:25,664
你前天说的半调子理论是什么?
Ray, what was that you were saying the other day about half-cocked theories?

367
00:31:25,749 --> 00:31:28,667
雷 好好睡
Ray... sleep tight.

368
00:32:36,149 --> 00:32:38,225
周三晚上不行 我要打保龄球
No way Wednesday night. I'm in a league.

369
00:32:38,318 --> 00:32:42,398
这场讲习会将改变你的一生 那个人是很棒的治疗师
This seminar could change your life, Vic. The man is a great healer.

370
00:32:42,489 --> 00:32:45,573
我是很棒的保龄球选手 周三晚上要对抗罗西利水电队
And I'm a great bowler. Wednesday night we're taking on Roselli Plumbing.

371
00:32:45,658 --> 00:32:48,066
你应该接触这个人
You should expose yourself to this guy, Vic.

372
00:32:48,161 --> 00:32:50,912
他了解超物理力量
He understands paraphysical forces...

373
00:32:50,996 --> 00:32:55,243
水晶的疗效和按手发功
the healing capabilities of crystals and the laying on of hands.

374
00:32:55,334 --> 00:32:58,288
你想试试按手发功吗?
You wanna try laying on some hands?

375
00:32:58,378 --> 00:33:01,249
收垃圾的 等等!
Wait! Hold it, garbies! Garbies!

376
00:33:01,340 --> 00:33:04,590
收垃圾的 等一下!
Garbagemen! Hold on a minute! Wait a sec!

377
00:33:04,676 --> 00:33:08,425
等等! 你在干什么?
<i>Wait! Wait! Wait! Hold it! What are you doin'?</i>

378
00:33:08,514 --> 00:33:10,754
- 我在清垃圾 - 你疯了吗?
- I'm emptying garbage. - Are you outta your mind?

379
00:33:10,848 --> 00:33:13,304
给我!
Give me that!

380
00:33:13,393 --> 00:33:16,844
- 住手! - 什么也没有
- Hey, cut that out! - There's nothing here.

381
00:33:16,938 --> 00:33:19,607
没有断手断脚
Not a finger, not a nose, nothing!

382
00:33:19,690 --> 00:33:21,932
- 把那个给我 - 拿去
- Give me that. - Here you go.

383
00:33:22,026 --> 00:33:25,110
- 你在干什么? - 你要我帮忙
- What are you doin'? - You asked me to help.

384
00:33:25,196 --> 00:33:27,105
你要打给谁?
Who you calling?

385
00:33:27,198 --> 00:33:29,518
我要打给德凡尼 要他们打小木屋打开
I'm calling the Delvaneys and having them open the cottage.

386
00:33:29,534 --> 00:33:32,106
我才不想去小木屋
No, Carol. I don't want to go to the cottage.

387
00:33:32,202 --> 00:33:34,954
好 大卫和我去 你留在这里当间谍
Fine. Then Dave and I will go and you can stay here and spy.

388
00:33:35,038 --> 00:33:36,947
没问题
Oh, all right. Okay.

389
00:33:37,040 --> 00:33:40,290
- 怎么? 你不高兴了? - 没有 去小木屋啊!
- What? What? Are you sulking now? - No, go up to the cottage!

390
00:33:40,377 --> 00:33:42,784
带大卫去小木屋 留我在家里走来走去
Take Dave and go to the cottage. Leave me to pad around the house.

391
00:33:42,879 --> 00:33:47,290
你成天就和那些傻瓜在街上晃来晃去
"Pad around the house"? All you do is pal around the neighbourhood With those two 

chuckleheads.

393
00:33:47,384 --> 00:33:49,626
- 我实在很担心你 - 为什么?
<i>- I am very, very worried about you. - Why?</i>

394
00:33:49,719 --> 00:33:52,470
- 看看你这副样子 - 我什么样子?
<i>- You're acting like... - What am I acting like, Carol?</i>

395
00:33:52,555 --> 00:33:54,464
我就像在休假的人  
Like a guy who's on vacation! 

396
00:33:54,557 --> 00:33:56,466
- 这才不像在休假 - 我很晚起床
- This is not someone on vacation! - See? I sleep late!

397
00:33:56,559 --> 00:33:58,468
- 那去晒晒太阳啊! - 穿睡衣怎么晒?
- Get a tan then! - In my pyjamas?

398
00:33:58,561 --> 00:34:00,802
我不晓得 
Fix the barbecue! I don't know!

399
00:34:00,896 --> 00:34:03,138
你去小木屋把自己晒黑 带大卫一起去 
You go to the cottage and get a tan! Take David with you!

400
00:34:03,232 --> 00:34:06,150
我不在乎! 我会吃外卖 我会洗衣服
I don't care! I'll eat takeout! I'll do the laundry myself!

401
00:34:06,235 --> 00:34:08,393
我会吸尘 房子会一尘不染
I'll vacuum the house! It'll be spotless!

402
00:34:08,487 --> 00:34:10,479
阿特把垃圾扔到街上
Art's throwing garbage all over the street.

403
00:34:10,572 --> 00:34:13,905
你妈妈和我正在谈话 如果你... 什么?
Your mom and I are having a conversation! If you... What?

404
00:34:13,992 --> 00:34:17,990
从垃圾车出来! 你发神经吗?
<i>Get out of the truck! Are you nuts?</i>

405
00:34:18,079 --> 00:34:20,155
一定在这里某个地方
Hey, it's gotta be in here somewhere.

406
00:34:20,248 --> 00:34:22,490
最高法庭裁决 一个人的垃圾一到路边
The Supreme Court ruled that a person's garbage...

407
00:34:22,584 --> 00:34:24,865
- 就属于公共领域 - 闭嘴
- is public domain the minute it hits the kerb. - Shut up.

408
00:34:24,919 --> 00:34:29,377
你们有没有碰到一个可能有点湿的超大垃圾袋?
Did you guys pick up a Hefty bag out of that yard that was bulky and probably a little moist?

410
00:34:29,466 --> 00:34:32,668
- 这些人怎么搞的? - 他有权利知道
- What is wrong with these people? - He has a right to know, Vic.

411
00:34:32,760 --> 00:34:36,342
别惹我 嘿 你可以帮我把这傢伙弄走吗?
Don't start up with me. Hey, could you help me get this guy out of here?

412
00:34:36,430 --> 00:34:38,339
怎么回事?
Hey, Art. What's happening?

413
00:34:41,351 --> 00:34:44,851
雷 回来!
No! Ray! Ray, come back here!

414
00:34:44,938 --> 00:34:47,061
只要等一... 我就会... 呀
Just one... I'll be... Yeah.

415
00:34:47,149 --> 00:34:49,355
你的薪水是靠我缴的税
My taxes pay your salary!

416
00:34:49,443 --> 00:34:51,684
我在也不想听你胡言乱语
I don't want to hear any of your bullshit either!

417
00:34:51,778 --> 00:34:53,854
这里的问题是垃圾以及谁来收拾这个烂摊子
The question here is garbage and who picks up this mess.

418
00:34:53,946 --> 00:34:56,354
"谁来收拾这个烂摊子"?
<i>"Who picks up this mess"?</i>

419
00:34:56,449 --> 00:35:00,529
你来收拾这个烂摊子 因为你是收垃圾的
You're gonna pick up the mess because you are a garbageman.

420
00:35:00,620 --> 00:35:03,027
我收的是桶子里的垃圾 不是街上的垃圾
I pick up garbage in cans, not from the street!

421
00:35:03,122 --> 00:35:05,198
雷 这里找不到
Ray, there's nothing in here.

422
00:35:05,291 --> 00:35:08,209
我们把整辆车翻遍了 他们一定掉包了
<i>We practically checked this whole truck. They must have switched on us.</i>

423
00:35:08,628 --> 00:35:10,287
- 联邦调查局? - 不 柯罗佩
<i>- The F.B.I.? - No, the Klopeks.</i>

424
00:35:10,378 --> 00:35:15,171
哎呀 淘气的小狗
Oh, no. Naughty little puppy.

425
00:35:17,094 --> 00:35:21,554
你到马克叔叔的草坪他会不高兴的
Uncle Markie gets very upset when you're on his lawn.

426
00:35:21,640 --> 00:35:26,218
等等 你全身脏兮兮的 而且一直在发抖
Wait a minute. You're all dirty, and you're shaking.

427
00:35:26,311 --> 00:35:29,727
瓦特知道你在外面吗?
I wonder if Walter knows you're outside.

428
00:35:29,815 --> 00:35:31,890
- 在雨中? - 是啊 当时在下雨
- In the rain? - Yeah, it was raining.

429
00:35:31,982 --> 00:35:34,390
- 总共有几个人? - 三个
- There were how many of them? - Well, uh, three.

430
00:35:34,485 --> 00:35:36,893
他们当时在做什么?
And what were they doing?

431
00:35:36,987 --> 00:35:39,063
- 他们在挖地 - 就像挖墓者!
- They were diggin'. - Digging! Like grave diggers!

432
00:35:39,156 --> 00:35:41,065
- 他们是食尸者! - 我可没说
- I told you! They're ghouls! - No, I didn't say that.

433
00:35:41,158 --> 00:35:42,569
他们可能在挖别的东西
They could have been digging for anything.

434
00:35:42,660 --> 00:35:44,902
他们可能在挖大蚯蚓
They could have been digging for night crawlers.

435
00:35:44,995 --> 00:35:48,246
- 大蚯蚓? - 他们是渔夫 他们需要鱼饵
- Night crawlers? - They're fishermen. They need bait.

436
00:35:48,332 --> 00:35:50,240
清醒过来 面对现实吧
Wake up and smell the coffee! 

437
00:35:50,333 --> 00:35:53,916
那小子昨晚看到我们趁我们睡觉时爬起来
The kid spotted us last night. When we were sleeping, he got up.

438
00:35:54,003 --> 00:35:56,921
走到垃圾筒旁边 拿起尸体然后...
He went to the garbage can, he took the body and then he...

439
00:35:57,006 --> 00:36:00,755
埋在自己的院子里
He buried him in the backyard.

440
00:36:00,844 --> 00:36:03,798
- 我们走吧 - 这个我喜欢
- Let's get outta here. - I like this.

441
00:36:03,888 --> 00:36:06,426
我讨厌死巷 只有一条出路 而且那些人好怪
I hate cul-de-sacs. There's only one way out, and the people are weird.

442
00:36:06,516 --> 00:36:09,683
赤裸的小姐
Naked ladies.

443
00:36:11,520 --> 00:36:15,103
有人知道瓦特把备用钥匙放在哪里吗?
Does anyone know if Walter left a spare key around anywhere?

444
00:36:15,190 --> 00:36:19,899
他出门时一定忘了喂昆妮
He must have gone away and forgot to feed Queenie.

445
00:36:21,697 --> 00:36:25,113
- 瓦特! - 我希望他没事
- Walter! - I hope nothing happened to him.

446
00:36:25,200 --> 00:36:28,450
- 我们应该打电话叫警察 - 这计划还真好啊
- I think we should call the police. - Oh, good plan, Ray.

447
00:36:28,537 --> 00:36:31,453
我看到那里有动静
I think I see something moving in there.

448
00:36:35,543 --> 00:36:38,295
你怎么进去的?
How did you get in there?

449
00:36:38,379 --> 00:36:43,456
士兵有本事解决难题 进来吧
<i>A soldier's way saves the day. Entrez.</i>

450
00:36:43,551 --> 00:36:46,967
- 真棒 亲爱的 - 真漂亮
<i>- Good, honey. - Beautiful.</i>

451
00:36:47,055 --> 00:36:49,462
瓦特? 
Walter? 

452
00:36:49,557 --> 00:36:51,798
- 看起来不妙 
This doesn't look good.

453
00:36:51,892 --> 00:36:54,299
有挣扎的迹象
There are signs of a struggle here.

454
00:36:54,394 --> 00:36:56,802
电视机开着 椅子翻倒
The TV's still on. Chairs turned over.

455
00:36:56,897 --> 00:36:59,470
我不会说那事挣扎的迹象
I wouldn't say that's a sign of a struggle.

456
00:36:59,566 --> 00:37:02,318
我应该上楼检查一下
I think I should go upstairs and check this out.

457
00:37:02,402 --> 00:37:04,976
也许老傢伙躺在楼上的浴缸里
Maybe the guy's upstairs in a bathtub or something...

458
00:37:05,072 --> 00:37:08,322
脑袋开花 到处都是血
cracked his head open, there's blood everywhere...

459
00:37:08,408 --> 00:37:10,649
楼上的东西都别碰 知道吗?
Just don't touch anything up there, all right?

460
00:37:10,743 --> 00:37:13,495
遵命 彼德森先生
Yes, sir, Mr Peterson.

461
00:37:13,579 --> 00:37:16,497
让我们看看有没有狗食
Let's see if we can find some dog food.

462
00:37:16,582 --> 00:37:20,331
我不喜欢在邻居家里偷偷摸摸的
I don't like this. I don't like snooping around a neighbour's house.

463
00:37:20,419 --> 00:37:23,337
你是说死人的家里?
You mean a dead guy's house?

464
00:37:23,422 --> 00:37:25,830
你想把口袋的东西拿出来吗?
You wanna take that out of your pocket?

465
00:37:25,925 --> 00:37:28,676
- 你可以不偷瓦特家的东西吗? - 有什么差别?
- You wanna not steal that from Walter's house? - Hey, what's the difference?

466
00:37:28,761 --> 00:37:31,595
反正这堆垃圾会流进跳蚤市场
All this junk is gonna end up in a flea market sooner or later.

467
00:37:31,679 --> 00:37:35,013
他可能走得匆忙 把狗忘记了
<i>He might have left in a hurry and forgot about the dog.</i>

468
00:37:35,100 --> 00:37:37,507
留在这里 我去找你的盘子
Okay, stay right here, and we'll find your dish.

469
00:37:37,602 --> 00:37:40,058


470
00:37:40,146 --> 00:37:42,388
正中红心!
Bull's-eye!

471
00:37:42,482 --> 00:37:44,391
什么?
What, what, what?

472
00:37:44,484 --> 00:37:46,441
那里有只死老鼠
A dead rat! There!

473
00:37:46,528 --> 00:37:49,363
亲爱的 那不是老鼠
Honey, that's not a rat.

474
00:37:49,447 --> 00:37:51,355
那是瓦特的假发
That's Walter's toupee.

475
00:37:51,448 --> 00:37:54,200
把假发放在炉子上 真是好位置
Beautiful place to keep a toupee: On the stove.

476
00:37:54,284 --> 00:37:56,194
我饿死了
I'm starving.

477
00:37:56,286 --> 00:37:59,204
我们知道这些老人家
One thing about these old guys:

478
00:37:59,289 --> 00:38:02,374
他们没戴假发是不会出门的
They don't ever leave the house without their hair.

479
00:38:02,459 --> 00:38:05,033
不对
No, sir.

480
00:38:06,797 --> 00:38:11,541
瓦特是在匆忙中离开房子的
Walter left this house in a big hurry.

481
00:38:11,634 --> 00:38:14,884
大伙来看! 这些饼干是...
<i>Hey, you guys, look! These cookies are...</i>

482
00:38:14,971 --> 00:38:17,378
好极了 大家出去!  
That's great! Everybody out!

483
00:38:17,473 --> 00:38:19,881
我们在一天之内已经触犯太多法律了
I think we've broken enough laws for one day.

